quran[82]{c,v,t}:
  100,9,Does he not know? When the contents of the graves are scattered around
  100,10,And the contents of the hearts are obtained
  100,11,"Their Lord, on that Day, is fully informed of them"
  101,1,The Shocker
  101,2,What is the Shocker
  101,3,What will explain to you what the Shocker is
  101,4,The Day when the people will be like scattered moths
  101,5,And the mountains will be like tufted wool
  101,6,As for he whose scales are heavy
  101,7,He will be in a pleasant life
  101,8,But as for he whose scales are light
  101,9,His home is the Abyss
  101,10,Do you know what it is
  101,11,A Raging Fire
  102,1,Abundance distracts you
  102,2,Until you visit the graveyards
  102,3,"Indeed, you will know"
  102,4,"Certainly, you will know"
  102,5,If you knew with knowledge of certainty
  102,6,You would see the Inferno
  102,7,Then you will see it with the eye of certainty
  102,8,"Then, on that Day, you will be questioned about the Bliss"
  103,1,By time
  103,2,The human being is in loss
  103,3,"Except those who believe, and do good works, and encourage truth, and recommend patience"
  104,1,Woe to every slanderer backbiter
  104,2,Who gathers wealth and counts it over
  104,3,Thinking that his wealth has made him immortal
  104,4,By no means. He will be thrown into the Crusher
  104,5,And what will make you realize what the Crusher is
  104,6,God's kindled Fire
  104,7,That laps to the hearts
  104,8,It closes in on them
  104,9,In extended columns
  105,1,Have you not considered how your Lord dealt with the People of the Elephant
  105,2,Did He not make their plan go wrong
  105,3,He sent against them swarms of birds
  105,4,Throwing at them rocks of baked clay
  105,5,Leaving them like chewed-up leaves
  106,1,For the security of Quraish
  106,2,Their security during winter and summer journeys
  106,3,Let them worship the Lord of this House
  106,4,"Who has fed them against hunger, and has secured them against fear"
  107,1,Have you considered him who denies the religion
  107,2,It is he who mistreats the orphan
  107,3,And does not encourage the feeding of the poor
  107,4,So woe to those who pray
  107,5,Those who are heedless of their prayers
  107,6,Those who put on the appearance
  107,7,And withhold the assistance
  108,1,We have given you plenty
  108,2,So pray to your Lord and sacrifice
  108,3,He who hates you is the loser
  109,1,"Say, 'O disbelievers"
  109,2,I do not worship what you worship
  109,3,Nor do you worship what I worship
  109,4,Nor do I serve what you serve
  109,5,Nor do you serve what I serve
  109,6,"You have your way, and I have my way"
  110,1,"When there comes God's victory, and conquest"
  110,2,And you see the people entering God's religion in multitudes
  110,3,"Then celebrate the praise of your Lord, and seek His forgiveness. He is the Accepter of Repentance"
  111,1,"Condemned are the hands of Abee Lahab, and he is condemned"
  111,2,"His wealth did not avail him, nor did what he acquired"
  111,3,He will burn in a Flaming Fire
  111,4,And his wife—the firewood carrier
  111,5,Around her neck is a rope of thorns
  112,1,"Say, 'He is God, the One"
  112,2,"God, the Absolute"
  112,3,"He begets not, nor was He begotten"
  112,4,And there is nothing comparable to Him
  113,1,"Say, 'I take refuge with the Lord of Daybreak"
  113,2,From the evil of what He created
  113,3,And from the evil of the darkness as it gathers
  113,4,And from the evil of those who practice sorcery
  113,5,And from the evil of an envious when he envies
  114,1,"Say, 'I seek refuge in the Lord of mankind"
  114,2,The King of mankind
  114,3,The God of mankind
  114,4,From the evil of the sneaky whisperer
  114,5,Who whispers into the hearts of people
  114,6,From among jinn and among people